article_title: China’s Rising Service Sector Won’t Ease Import Pain, Report Says
article_text:
China’s declining industrial sector is driving down imports from trading partners and the country’s growing service sector isn’t likely to compensate for those losses, researchers with the Federal Reserve Bank of San Francisco say.

“The service sector relies much less on imported intermediate inputs than other sectors,” San Francisco Federal Reserve researcher Mark Spiegel wrote in an economic letter Monday. As a result, “service...
